## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of up-to-date data and the inherent complexity of global energy markets. The dynamic nature of geopolitical and economic factors means that the causes of fuel shortages can evolve rapidly. Additionally, while this report provides a broad overview, specific regional factors may also play a significant role in fuel shortages, which are not covered in detail here. Further research is recommended to explore these regional dynamics and their impact on global fuel supply.